title: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not returning the expected output 'MySomeClass'.
OB: When calling the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method with a classSet parameter, the current output is 'MySomeClass'.
EB: However, I expect the output to be 'MySomeClass'. This behavior is not yet implemented according to the Servlet 3.0 specification.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Call the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method.
2. Pass a classSet parameter.
3. Verify that the output is 'MySomeClass' instead of the expected 'MySomeClass'.
